SUMMARY:Petaluma before Columbus: Exploring a model of indigenous regenera
 tive sustainability
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T180000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T193000
UID:d184996acf58c16cbc97df14ce6d21cf@sonomalibrary.org
DESCRIPTION:Spanish explorers saw California as an Eden with abundant plan
 t and animal life because Native Californians intentionally and sustainabl
 y managed their environment in cooperation with nature for over 12\,000 ye
 ars.
LOCATION:Petaluma Meeting Room at Petaluma Regional Library
URL:https://events.sonomalibrary.org/event/petaluma-columbus-indigenous-re
 generative-sustainability-106950
X-SOURCE:Petaluma Regional Library
END:VEVENT
